DJIA

2023-03-13

The Dow Jones Industrial Average (DJIA), Dow Jones, or simply the Dow, is a stock market index of 30 prominent companies listed on stock exchanges in the United States. Firstly, by consulting EDA on DJIA, we try to answer the following questions. How have yields and trading volumes changed over the years? How have yields and trading volumes fluctuated over the years?

chartSeries(DJI, type = "bars", theme="white")

We analyze the adjusted closing prices here.

dj_close <- DJI[,"DJI.Adjusted"]

The definition of return:\(R_t=\frac{P_t-P_{t-1}}{P_{t-1}}=\frac{P_t}{P_{t-1}}-1\). The definition of log-return:\(r_t=ln\frac{P_t}{P_t-1}=ln(1+R_t)\). We calculate the log-return.

dj_ret <- CalculateReturns(dj_close, method = "log")
dj_ret <- na.omit(dj_ret)

We need some auxiliary functions to simplify some basic data conversion, summarization, and plotting.

# 1.从xts转换为带有year and value列的数据框。这样就可以进行年度总结和绘制。
xts_to_dataframe <- function(data_xts) {
  df_t <- data.frame(year = factor(year(index(data_xts))), value = coredata(data_xts))
  colnames(df_t) <- c( "year", "value")
  df_t
}

# 2.摘要统计信息，用于存储为数据框列的数据。
bs_rn <- rownames(basicStats(rnorm(10,0,1))) # 基本统计数据输出行名称
dataframe_basicstats <- function(dataset) {
  result <- with(dataset, tapply(value, year, basicStats))
  df_result <- do.call(cbind, result)
  rownames(df_result) <- bs_rn
  as.data.frame(df_result)
}

# 3.返回关联的列名。
filter_dj_stats <- function(dataset_basicstats, metricname, threshold) {
  r <- which(rownames(dataset_basicstats) ==  metricname)
  colnames(dataset_basicstats[r, which(dataset_basicstats[r,] > threshold), drop = FALSE])
}

# 4.基于年的面板箱线图。
dataframe_boxplot <- function(dataset, title) {
  p <- ggplot(data = dataset, aes(x = year, y = value)) + theme_bw() + theme(legend.position = "none") + geom_boxplot(fill = "lightblue")
  p <- p + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1)) + ggtitle(title) + ylab("year")
  p
}

# 5.密度图，以年份为基准。
dataframe_densityplot <- function(dataset, title) {
  p <- ggplot(data = dataset, aes(x = value)) + geom_density(fill = "lightblue") 
  p <- p + facet_wrap(. ~ year)
  p <- p + theme_bw() + theme(legend.position = "none") + ggtitle(title)
  p
}

# 6.基于年份的QQ图。
dataframe_qqplot <- function(dataset, title) {
  p <- ggplot(data = dataset, aes(sample = value)) + stat_qq(colour = "blue") + stat_qq_line() 
  p <- p + facet_wrap(. ~ year)
  p <- p + theme_bw() + theme(legend.position = "none") + ggtitle(title)
  p
}

# 7. Shapiro测试
shp_pvalue <- function (v) {
  shapiro.test(v)$p.value
}
dataframe_shapirotest <- function(dataset) {
  result <- with(dataset, tapply(value, year, shp_pvalue))
  as.data.frame(result)
}

###Exploratory data analysis of weekly log-return We can calculate the weekly log-return by starting with the daily log-return. We analyze the trading week of {t-4, t-3, t-2, t-1, t} days and know the closing price on day t-5 (the last day of the previous week). We define the weekly logarithmic return as: \(r_t^w=ln\frac{P_t}{P_{t-5}}=ln\frac{P_tP_{t-1}P_{t-2}P_{t-3}P_{t-4}}{P_{t-1}P_{t-2}P_{t-3}P_{t-4}P_{t-5}}=ln\frac{P_t}{P_{t-1}}+ln\frac{P_{t-1}}{P_{t-2}}+ln\frac{P_{t-2}}{P_{t-3}}+ln\frac{P_{t-3}}{P_{t-4}}+ln\frac{P_{t-4}}{P_{t-5}}=r_t+r_{t-1}+r_{t-2}+r_{t-3}+r_{t-4}\)

dj_weekly_ret <- apply.weekly(dj_ret, sum)
plot(dj_weekly_ret)

dj_weekly_ret_df <- xts_to_dataframe(dj_weekly_ret)

Similar to log-return, we can define the log-ratio of trading volume as: \(v_t=ln\frac{V_t}{V_{t-1}}\) We can calculate and graph it through the “CalculateReturns” in the “PerformanceAnalytics” package.

dj_vol_log_ratio <- CalculateReturns(dj_vol, "log")
dj_vol_log_ratio <- na.omit(dj_vol_log_ratio)
plot(dj_vol_log_ratio)
